 the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Thomas Monington was born in 1455, in Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England, his father, Richard Monington, was 25 and his mother, Ellen Walwyn, was 29. He had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Elizabeth Milbourne. He died in 1497, in Sarnesfield, Herefordshire, England, at the age of 42, and was buried in Sarnesfield, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1455–1497":"1455–1497","1454–Male":"1454–Surnud","1474–1527":"1474–1527","1492–1551":"1492–1551","1511–1551":"1511–1551","–1532":"–1532","–Male":"Surnud","1518–1600":"1518–1600","1430–Male":"1430–Surnud","1426–1466":"1426–1466","1492":"1492","1426":"1426","1600":"1600","1511":"1511","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1532":"1532","1454":"1454","1497":"1497","1430":"1430","1551":"1551","1474":"1474","1518":"1518","1527":"1527","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sarnesfield, Herefordshire, England":"Sarnesfield, Herefordshire, England","Saint Mary Churchyard, Sarnesfield, Herefordshire, England":"Sarnesfield, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1455–1497":"1455–1497","1454–Male":"1454–Kuollut","1474–1527":"1474–1527","1492–1551":"1492–1551","1511–1551":"1511–1551","–1532":"–1532","–Male":"Kuollut","1518–1600":"1518–1600","1430–Male":"1430–Kuollut","1426–1466":"1426–1466","1492":"1492","1426":"1426","1600":"1600","1511":"151